<definition id="fs-idm10958256">
<term>Americanization</term>
<meaning id="fs-idm10933168">the policy aimed at assimilating Native Americans into a middle class, Protestant version of the American way of life through boarding schools for Native American children and land allotment for Native American households</meaning>
</definition>
<definition id="fs-idp6623360">
<term>Wounded Knee Massacre</term>
<meaning id="fs-idp4604016">an attempt to disarm a group of Lakota people near Wounded Knee, South Dakota, which resulted in members of the Seventh Cavalry of the U.S. Army opening fire and killing over 150 Lakota</meaning>
</definition>
<definition id="fs-idm31182384">
<term>Sand Creek Massacre</term>
<meaning id="fs-idp33237472">a militia raid led by Colonel Chivington on a Cheyenne and Arapaho peoples camp in Colorado, flying both the American flag and the white flag of surrender; over one hundred men, women, and children were killed</meaning>
</definition>
